validation of assessment methods, integration of non-technical skills, consideration of human factors,
and the adaptation of existing frameworks for the European context. The identified knowledge gaps and
potential future research directions provide a roadmap for further research in consolidating cybersecurity
job profiles assessment in Europe. By addressing these gaps, policymakers and educators can develop
effective strategies for educating and training cybersecurity professionals with the required competencies
to tackle emerging cybersecurity challenges.

